{"schemaVersion":1,"bookId":"toefl-sentences","unitId":"sentence-058","title":"Sentence 58","sectionId":"sentences-051","sectionTitle":"Sentence 51-60","pageStart":380,"pageEnd":385,"extractionMethod":"text-layer","wordEntryCount":28,"duplicateEntryCount":4,"pages":[{"number":380,"blocks":[{"type":"title","text":"Sentence 58"},{"type":"text","text":"We’ve gone over where coral reefs are usually formed—along the"},{"type":"text","text":"edges of shallow ocean banks in tropical or subtropical regions, and the"},{"type":"text","text":"fact that they are declining at an alarming rate."},{"type":"text","text":"我们已经讲过珊瑚礁通常在哪里形成——沿着热带或亚热带地"},{"type":"text","text":"区浅海沿岸的边缘地带——以及珊瑚礁正在以让人担忧的速度消失"},{"type":"text","text":"这一事实。"},{"type":"section","text":"语法笔记"},{"type":"text","text":"本句主干是“We’ve gone over where ... and the fact that ...”。句中的"},{"type":"text","text":"where coral reefs are usually formed和“the fact that ...”是并列成分，一起"},{"type":"text","text":"作主句的宾语，其中where引导宾语从句，that引导the fact的同位语从"},{"type":"text","text":"句。破折号后面的along the edges of shallow ocean banks in tropical or"},{"type":"text","text":"subtropical regions是解释说明前面提到的where coral reefs are usually"},{"type":"text","text":"formed。"},{"type":"section","text":"核心词表"},{"type":"entry","text":"coral /ˈkɔːrəl/ n. 珊瑚（虫） a. 珊瑚色的","headword":"coral"},{"type":"note","text":"搭配 coral reef 珊瑚礁"},{"type":"entry","text":"shallow /ˈʃæloʊ/ a. 浅的；浅薄的","headword":"shallow"}]},{"number":381,"blocks":[{"type":"definition","text":"n. 浅滩，浅水处"},{"type":"note","text":"记忆 容许（allow）到浅水处（shallow）玩耍"},{"type":"note","text":"搭配 shallow water 浅水区"},{"type":"note","text":"同义 superficial a. 浅的；肤浅的"},{"type":"entry","text":"tropical /ˈtrɑːpɪkl/ a. 热带的","headword":"tropical"},{"type":"note","text":"搭配 tropical forest 热带雨林"},{"type":"note","text":"同根 tropic n. 热带地区"},{"type":"entry","text":"subtropical /ˌsʌbˈtrɑːpɪkl/ a. 亚热带的","headword":"subtropical"},{"type":"note","text":"搭配 subtropical climate 亚热带气候"},{"type":"entry","text":"decline /dɪˈklaɪn/ n./vi. 下降；衰退","headword":"decline"},{"type":"note","text":"搭配 decline stage 衰退时期"},{"type":"note","text":"同根 declining a. 下降的，衰退的"},{"type":"entry","text":"alarming /əˈlɑːrmɪŋ/ a. 令人担忧的；使人惊恐的","headword":"alarming"},{"type":"note","text":"同根 alarm vt. 使惊恐，惊动"},{"type":"text","text":"alarmist n. 杞人忧天者"},{"type":"section","text":"主题归纳"}]},{"number":382,"blocks":[{"type":"text","text":"与“珊瑚礁”相关的词："},{"type":"entry","text":"acidification /əˌsɪdəfɪ'keʃən/ n. 酸化","headword":"acidification"},{"type":"note","text":"搭配 oceanic acidification 海洋酸化"},{"type":"entry","text":"atoll /ˈætɔːl/ n. 环状珊瑚岛；环礁","headword":"atoll"},{"type":"text","text":"blast fishing 爆破捕鱼"},{"type":"text","text":"calcium carbonate 碳酸钙"},{"type":"text","text":"climate change 气候变化"},{"type":"entry","text":"crustacean /krʌˈsteɪʃn/ n. 甲壳类动物","headword":"crustacean"},{"type":"definition","text":"a. 甲壳类的"}]},{"number":383,"blocks":[{"type":"note","text":"记忆 crust（外壳）＋acean→甲壳类动物"},{"type":"entry","text":"exoskeleton /ˈeksoʊskelɪtn/ n. 外骨骼","headword":"exoskeleton"},{"type":"note","text":"记忆 exo（外部）+skeleton（骨骼）→外骨骼"},{"type":"entry","text":"fishery /ˈfɪʃəri/ n. 渔业；水产业","headword":"fishery"},{"type":"note","text":"搭配 fishery resource 渔业资源"},{"type":"text","text":"fore reef 前礁"},{"type":"entry","text":"fragile /ˈfrædʒl/ a. 脆弱的","headword":"fragile"},{"type":"note","text":"搭配 fragile ecosystem 脆弱的生态系统"},{"type":"text","text":"fringing reef 岸礁；边礁"},{"type":"entry","text":"jellyfish /ˈdʒelifɪʃ/ n. 海蜇；水母","headword":"jellyfish"},{"type":"note","text":"记忆 jelly（果冻）+fish（鱼）→果冻一样透明的鱼→水母"},{"type":"text","text":"marine species海洋物种"},{"type":"entry","text":"mollusk /ˈmɑːləsk/ n. 软体动物","headword":"mollusk"},{"type":"note","text":"记忆 moll（软）＋usk→软体动物"},{"type":"entry","text":"polyp /ˈpɑːlɪp/ n. （水螅型）珊瑚虫；水螅（体）","headword":"polyp"},{"type":"text","text":"rainforests of the sea 海洋热带雨林"},{"type":"text","text":"reef crest 礁顶"},{"type":"text","text":"sea anemone 海葵"},{"type":"entry","text":"sponge /spʌndʒ/ n. [动]海绵","headword"